<br>
She spoke my guild name and then once more, shook her head in disgust at my husband, who is a Dark Elf. She asked what he was doing, to which he didn't reply as he was busy teaching both my daughter and I new languages. I sent her a personal tell and enlightend her that he was teaching us ( his wife and daughter) languages and asked her why she inquired.<br>
She then retorted 'Wife and Daughter??? thats even worse!'<br>
<br>
It was quite obvious at this point that she had a problem with the fact that my husband, a dark elven Necromancer had married me, a wood elven Druidess. <br>
<br>
My question is - who is she to judge? It may not be her personal choice but what right does she have to dictate who can and can not fall in love? I was sickend by her biggot attitude and the way she took it upon herself to spread her misery to people who'd never done anything deserving of it.<br>
<br>
To this Dark Elven Enchanter of 58 seasons I say this -<br>
There is a difference between being a biggot and roleplaying. Being rude to another person just because you dont agree with the way they live their lives is not accpetable under any circumstances, Especially not if it doesnt affect you in any way. If you dont like it, move on. I pitty people like you.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=757539" target="top">Korynna Shadowhawk</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->-Proud Mommy to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=773913">Julyete</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
